2. docs/CANOPY_CHECKLIST.md

# Canopy Checklist
Use this checklist before promoting any claim, module, workflow, or doctrine into operational use.
## 1. Claim Definition
- [ ] Is the claim stated clearly?
- [ ] Is it falsifiable?
- [ ] Is the scope bounded?
## 2. Measurement
- [ ] What observable outcome would support the claim?
- [ ] What observable outcome would weaken or falsify it?
- [ ] What metric(s) are being used?
- [ ] What threshold counts as success?
## 3. Test Design
- [ ] Are the inputs defined?
- [ ] Is the procedure repeatable?
- [ ] Is there a baseline or comparison condition?
- [ ] Are known confounders listed?
## 4. Provenance
- [ ] Is the test run logged?
- [ ] Are assumptions recorded?
- [ ] Is the version / commit / config recorded?
- [ ] Is reviewer identity recorded?
## 5. Outcome
- [ ] Pass
- [ ] Fail
- [ ] Mixed / needs refinement
## 6. Canon Status
- [ ] Remains speculative
- [ ] Graduates to tested
- [ ] Graduates to validated
- [ ] Retired / archived

